detaileddescription.para: The group-id of the reporters of this class. This ID resembles group-identification and ordering information inside a group. The HTML output classes order Reporters by groups of hundred ID numbers. So i.e. all Distributions have Reporters with GroupID's in the range between 100 and 199. Highest numbers are always listed first. If in a sequence of Reporters its GroupID is in another century range, the HTML output will automatically insert a horizontal ruler and a new heading to indicate the new group of Reportable ModelComponents.

entry.para: ModelReporter. Highest number possible, so always first in order. Ensures that SubModelReporter will be printed before other Reportables in the main model report.
SimulationrunReporter, including Experiment duration and other important information referring to the experiment as whole.
Free for additional Reporters of new constructs that will be listed before the StatisticObjects used in a Model.
Reporters for StatisticObjects as the Accumulate, Tally, TextHistogram, Histogram, Regression and Count, which will be listed before the process synchronisation constructs used in the Model.

Additional Reporters for process synchronisation constructs as the Bin, Stock, Entrepot, Res, CondQueue, WaitQueue, Transporter and WorkStation, which will be listed before the Queues used in a Model.
Free for additional Reporters of new constructs that will be listed before the Queues used in a Model.
Queues. Queue will be sorted first, ProcessQueue last
Distributions. The generic DistributionReporter will be last with its GroupID of 100.
Free for additional Reporters of new constructs that will be listed after the Queues used in a Model.

detaileddescription.para: The column headings of this reporter. Reporters of the same group always have the same column headings. Entries should contain in the elements in the same order as the entries[].
The data entries of this reporter. Reporters of the same group always have the same number of entries. Entries should contain in the data elements in the same order as defined in the columns[] array.
The group's heading of this class of reporters. The String containe here is used as a table heading. All reporters of the same group must have the same group heading.
The Reportable that this reporter generates the report about
The number of columns this reporter produces.

Returns the heading for the group this reporter belongs to. This can easily be used as a heading in the reporter to introduce a new group of reporters.

detaileddescription.para: Declares the basic methods needed for reporter to be able to print reports about a model component. Since individual components need individual reports each component has to specify a special reporter to print its data. Derive from this class to implement the reporter for the specific Reportable class.
